cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the creation of dialogue agents. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a paradigm shift in the creation of goal-oriented complex dialogue systems. Additionally, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it mentions the limitations of end-to-end machine learning systems in creating deployable and verifiable dialogue agents. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it proposes a new approach to creating dialogue agents that covers all aspects of the process, from model solicitation to execution. Finally, it could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it introduces a robust executor for generalized contingent plans.
